    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi @safeimuslim and thanks for opening this issue. \r\n\r\nFrom [StackOverflow](https://stackoverflow.com/a/48579915/654253):\r\n\r\nThe infiniteHits has very little logic in it. Here is what I'll do:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\n    // custom widget\r\n    var customInfiniteHits = instantsearch.connectors.connectInfiniteHits(function(options, isFirstRendering) {\r\n      var showMore = options.showMore;\r\n      var hits = options.hits;\r\n      var containerNode = otpions.widgetParams.containerNode;\r\n    \r\n      if(isFirstRendering) {\r\n        bindScroll(showMore);\r\n      }\r\n    \r\n      containerNode.html(\r\n        hits.map(function(hit) {\r\n          return '<div>' + hit._highlightResult.name.value + '</div>';\r\n        })\r\n      );\r\n    });\r\n    \r\n    // Usage\r\n    search.addWidget(\r\n      customInfiniteHits({\r\n        containerNode: $('#custom-infinite-hits-container'),\r\n      })\r\n    );\r\n```\r\n\r\n`bindScroll` is the function that will listen to scroll position and will call the `showMore` provided. This function does not take parameters.",
